Hey Doc:<br>
     Yes, I guess it was overkill-only due to anger and fustration on your idiotic comment.  If you want to talk-why insult us that served.  I didn't serve to kill people (in war survival does come to mind though), I was placed in that situation thanks to Uncle Sam.  In regards to my medals-no I won't stop wearing them, even if they offend or anger someone.  I was part of a unit working with the Vietnamese people and I earned a few medals for service and dedicated service-no John Wayne or Rambo-no extreme heroism-just being there and fighting to help my buddies stay alive.  I don't know what your anger is over medals, maybe you can tell us your real feeling instead of the rhetoric you gave before.  I don't throw my medals in everyone's face. I have them hanging up in my home and they represent a time in my life that I AM PROUD OF. Listen Doc-I never attacked a peace protestor-May not have liked what some did, but never attacked one.  If you are for healing for all of this wounded generation, then WHY attack us for displaying our medals.  My medals are the only thing Uncle Sam ever gave to me.  They represent a time in my life where feelings were high and I served with some of the best friends I ever had.  They were not for killing babies or women, they were for being there to help my buddies.  I never asked for a parade, parties or a hero's homecoming-if I wear my medals, I wear them for those 58,000 young men of our generation that never came back and can't wear their own.  In the future, don't make blanket statements when you don't know the stories and the feelings each of us carries with us.  How about you tell us why you are so mad, that you attack like that, after many of us here have been open to hear your point of view.  How about you come out of you cave and talk to us?? 
<p><code>--   (Prophet ) </code><p>


